Hi Felix,

This is from our architect:

Cheers,


Justin


We are now working on a project to convert an office space, in a mixed-use building, to a Sole Occupancy Unit (SOU). We are adding a mezzanine level and require:
•	Mechanical ventilation design for wet areas (bathroom, kitchen & laundry)
•	Heating cooling.
Please note that the building has risers and existing services, but these would most likely need to be upgraded.

I have attached the DA Approval and the PCA's requirements (check items 47 & 51) and also note requirements for fire separation of any penetrations for ducts, and condensate pipework through SOU. The design fee would also need to include certification as per the Design Regulations of Dept. of Fair Trading. 

Let me know if you require any further information or a site inspection.

Cheers,
